eNCA's Lindokuhle Xulu reports. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police officers will soon be able to do their jobs, with one less burden. COVID-19 vaccinations for all 180,000 of them have now kicked off. READ: COVID-19 Vaccine: The homeless to get the jab Over 30,000 SAPS members have been infected and 680 have succumbed to COVID-19. Some who lined up on Monday have described the trauma of losing colleagues to the virus. eNCA's Lindokuhle Xulu shares more details in the video above.